  <header>
    
      <h1 class="entry-title">Rspec and Spork</h1>
    
    
      <p class="meta">
        








  


<time datetime="2012-09-28T00:00:00+01:00" pubdate data-updated="true">Sep 28<span>th</span>, 2012</time>
        
      </p>
    
  </header>


<div class="entry-content"><p>Rspec testing are getting annoying, there is too much wait time. So I found <a href="https://github.com/sporkrb/spork">Spork</a> and I gave it a try. I&#8217;ve run <code>time rspec spec --drb</code> and here is the before and afeter.</p>

<!--more-->


<p>The before</p>

<pre><code>Finished in 1.58 seconds
54 examples, 0 failures

real    0m6.372s
user    0m5.519s
sys 0m0.819s
</code></pre>

<p>And after</p>

<pre><code>Finished in 2.01 seconds
54 examples, 0 failures

real    0m2.568s
user    0m0.304s
sys 0m0.061s
</code></pre>

<p>The after is about 30% of the before! Yes, it&#8217;s worth it.</p>
</div>


